1
00:00:08,041 --> 00:00:09,666
[KURO]
All right, I admit it.

2
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:14,166
This is a pretty nice place to
get away from it all and unwind.

3
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:17,000
To take some time to relax
my body and mind.

4
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:19,125
[MAHIRU]
Kuro! Where'd you go?

5
00:00:19,208 --> 00:00:20,583
I know you're here somewhere!

6
00:00:20,666 --> 00:00:22,541
He's totally wrecking the vibe.

7
00:00:23,583 --> 00:00:25,916
I hope I'm not intruding.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,666
[MAHIRU]
Huh? Misono?!

9
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:29,125
Where did that bed come from?

10
00:00:29,208 --> 00:00:30,791
You didn't expect me
to sleep on some

11
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:32,583
cheap futon mattress, did you?

12
00:00:32,666 --> 00:00:33,750
Yeah, sure.

13
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,500
Will you remind me
who you are again, kid?

14
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:36,833
[MISONO]
Who are you calling a kid?!

15
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:39,666
I'm Misono Alicein,
Eve of the Servamp of Lust.

16
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,708
Sorry, but we enjoyed
a bath without you.

17
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,333
I couldn't be more relaxed.

18
00:00:43,416 --> 00:00:46,000
We're not here on
some kind of vacation!

19
00:00:46,083 --> 00:00:48,291
Am I the only one
taking this seriously?

20
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,666
[MAHIRU]
I don't get it.

21
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:23,958
How is everyone acting
so calm right now?

22
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,875
We have no idea what
Tsubaki's planning to do next.

23
00:02:26,958 --> 00:02:29,166
We don't even know
what our next move is.

24
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:32,916
Push the button
and soda comes out.

25
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,500
It's that simple.

26
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:37,250
[MAHIRU]
Thinking rationally...

27
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,666
What we really need
now is information.

28
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,958
Maybe we could catch one
of Tsubaki's subclasses

29
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:44,166
and convince them to shed
some light on what he's doing

30
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:46,375
and where he's hiding.

31
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:47,750
That's not a bad idea.

32
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:49,500
When it comes down to it,
we don't actually know

33
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:50,791
anything about him.

34
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:53,291
Or much about Servamps
in general, really.

35
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:56,208
You should ask him
about our organization

36
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:58,375
the next time you see him.

37
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:00,250
[MAHIRU] Knowing a little
about vampire history

38
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,416
could end up being
really helpful.

39
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,500
You think so?

40
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:04,791
Hey, you know what?

41
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:06,916
I bet that traveling
antique dealer knows more.

42
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,541
The one who showed up
with the Servamp of Envy.

43
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:12,458
It sounded to me like he knew
a whole lot about vampires.

44
00:03:12,541 --> 00:03:14,750
[MISONO] You can't put
your faith in that man.

45
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,166
[MAHIRU]
Why not?

46
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,458
He's just...

47
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:20,916
Never mind, forget it.

48
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,625
We'll be fine on our own.

49
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:27,083
[HUGH] Make way for
Pride's perfect landing!

50
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:29,375
Hugh! Where did you fly off to?

51
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,875
One of my subclasses
has new information.

52
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:34,708
It might be of some interest.

53
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:36,166
[MAHIRU]
A suspicious person?

54
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,250
[SAGAMI]
Yeah, and he's really strong.

55
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:40,500
I saw him beat up a
subclass like it was nothing,

56
00:03:40,583 --> 00:03:41,958
and then he just flew away.

57
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,000
He disappeared into the air!

58
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:44,833
He flew?

59
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:46,083
[SAGAMI]
Yeah.

60
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:47,750
He was wearing stylish
boots and dark clothes

61
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,750
and had big wings on his back.

62
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:50,958
You can't miss 'em.

63
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,875
[MAHIRU]
That's the guy?

64
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:56,166
This kid kinda reeks of danger.

65
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:57,791
We shouldn't get involved.

66
00:03:57,875 --> 00:03:59,041
Yeah, but what if
he knows something

67
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:00,458
that could lead us to Tsubaki?

68
00:04:02,166 --> 00:04:04,083
--[MAHIRU] A hedgehog?
--[KURO] Oh.

69
00:04:04,166 --> 00:04:05,125
What is it, Kuro?

70
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,208
I know him.

71
00:04:06,291 --> 00:04:08,458
Don't tell me it's
another Servamp.

72
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:10,375
Is he asking us to save him?

73
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:12,291
Why's he in a cage?
We're finding out.

74
00:04:12,375 --> 00:04:14,541
[KURO]
C'mon, this is a bad idea.

75
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,375
[MAHIRU] You have to learn to
put more faith in our allies.

76
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,875
And trusting their
subclasses, too.

77
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:23,791
Speaking of which,
where are your subclasses?

78
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:27,041
[KURO] I don't have any.
They're too much trouble.

79
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:28,458
In order to make a subclass,

80
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:29,916
you have to give
your blood to a human

81
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,500
on the brink of death.

82
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:34,458
But how do you know if a person
really wants to live any longer?

83
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:37,041
Maybe they wanna die.

84
00:04:37,125 --> 00:04:39,916
It's a complicated business.

85
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,291
Thinking about it
makes my head hurt.

86
00:04:42,375 --> 00:04:44,291
That's all I have to say.

87
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:45,625
[MAHIRU]
I see.

88
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:48,458
So that's why he doesn't
have any subclasses.

89
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:50,000
But why do I get the
feeling there's more

90
00:04:50,083 --> 00:04:51,541
he's not telling me?

91
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,875
[KURO] You sure you're going
to be all right doing this?

92
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,750
Tailing someone
alone is dangerous.

93
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:57,083
[MAHIRU]
I'm not alone.

94
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:59,166
You're here,
so that makes two of us.

95
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:01,083
I may not be much
help to you yet,

96
00:05:01,166 --> 00:05:04,458
but I want us to
become a real team.

97
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:07,375
That means you and I have
to be honest with each other.

98
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:09,250
Whenever you feel like talking,
I want to get to know

99
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,416
more about you.

100
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,083
But I'll wait until
you're comfortable.

101
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,750
[KURO]
I can't face this right now.

102
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,500
You're sure we've
got to follow him?

103
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:22,250
[MAHIRU] Well, Tetsu is big but
he's still a middle schooler.

104
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:25,166
And Misono just got out
of the hospital, so...

105
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:27,666
Thinking simply, we're the
only ones who can do this.

106
00:05:31,875 --> 00:05:33,125
[MAHIRU gasps]

107
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:36,541
Tell me what you are.
Are you angel? Or a demon?

108
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:38,458
Crap, he already noticed us!

109
00:05:38,541 --> 00:05:39,666
Way to go.

110
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:48,791
[piano music]

111
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:51,666
A piano? What is this, huh?

112
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:52,833
Kuro?

113
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,916
My body feels heavy.

114
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,708
[LICHT]
Ah, so you're the demon.

115
00:05:58,208 --> 00:05:59,250
[MAHIRU]
Kuro!

116
00:06:00,583 --> 00:06:03,083
[MAHIRU]
He's fast! And so strong!

117
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:06,000
Kuro's getting
thrashed up there!

118
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:08,666
You better fly, otherwise what's
the use of having a broom?

119
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:13,625
[KURO] My body's not bouncing
back as fast as it should.

120
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,416
Just what is this guy?

121
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,000
What's he doing to me?

122
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:19,791
[MAHIRU]
Kuro!

123
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:27,166
What did you do
to my partner?

124
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:29,583
And why do you have
a Servamp in a cage?

125
00:06:29,666 --> 00:06:31,416
You can have it
if you want it.

126
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,333
To be honest with you, I've been
trying to get rid of him.

127
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,416
[LAWLESS]
O, speak again, bright angel!

128
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,666
For thou art as glorious
to this night,

129
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:45,458
being o'er my head as is a
winged messenger of heaven.

130
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:47,041
That's by Shakespeare.

131
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:50,916
I'm the fifth Servamp
Lawless of Greed.

132
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,166
But you can call me Law-ly,

133
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,750
or leading man, or
whatever you want. Okay?

134
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,208
And this gloomy angel
with a penchant for violence

135
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,416
is my Eve, a real maestro.

136
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,958
Eighteen-year-old Jekylland
Licht Todoroki.

137
00:07:02,041 --> 00:07:04,416
Why are you describing me
as though we like each other?

138
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,041
Aw, come on, angel cakes.

139
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,791
I just figured I'd do
the introductions

140
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:09,625
since you're so shy
and you'd probably get

141
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:12,166
all mopey if you
had to talk about--Ah!

142
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,375
[screams]

143
00:07:13,458 --> 00:07:14,541
[MAHIRU]
What are you doing?!

144
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:15,833
[LICHT]
I hate that guy.

145
00:07:15,916 --> 00:07:17,916
Wait, but he's
your partner, right?

146
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,208
How can you hate him?

147
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:20,958
Well, see, it's because...

148
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:23,166
...I'm an angel.

149
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:27,416
That's right!
My reclusive little angel babe!

150
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,541
You're so amazing, in every way!

151
00:07:29,625 --> 00:07:31,375
He's the last angel
to travel to Earth.

152
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:32,750
We are not worthy!

153
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,750
[LICHT]
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

154
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,125
And die!

155
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:37,791
[MAHIRU] I thought we'd met
all the weirdos already.

156
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:39,583
So he's a violent angel.

157
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:41,541
This is just too much.

158
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:43,000
[MAHIRU]
Look at the bright side.

159
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,375
We've gained some new allies!

160
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:46,083
[LAWLESS]
No, no, you're mistaken.

161
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:48,041
I have no plans
to work with you.

162
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:50,666
Besides, what do you
need allies for?

163
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:52,958
[LAWLESS] After all, once
Big Brother makes a decision,

164
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:55,083
he can handle everything
himself, right?

165
00:07:56,666 --> 00:08:00,166
[LAWLESS] Should we kill
Tsubaki or leave him be?

166
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,541
Let's take a majority vote!

167
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:03,833
It'll be just like
the last time. Eh?

168
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:06,000
You really haven't
changed in all these years,

169
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:07,833
have you, Big Brother Sloth?

170
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:09,750
And that's not a compliment.

171
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:15,291
[MAHIRU] Hey, wait,
where are you going?

172
00:08:15,375 --> 00:08:17,125
[grunts]
You can't fly off already.

173
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:18,375
We're not done here yet.

174
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,500
What does a demon's
ally want with me?

175
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,000
We need your help with this.

176
00:08:22,083 --> 00:08:24,000
If we're gonna take Tsubaki
down, we need all the power

177
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:25,208
we can get on our side.

178
00:08:25,291 --> 00:08:28,000
Tsubaki?
Isn't that a flower's name?

179
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,291
You don't know?

180
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:30,500
I figured you attacked us
because you thought

181
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:31,625
we were with him.

182
00:08:31,708 --> 00:08:33,666
I'll tell you why I attacked.

183
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:36,250
It's just who I am--an angel.

184
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,791
[LAWLESS]
Yes, right, an angel.

185
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:39,541
[MAHIRU]
That's not gonna get old at all.

186
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:41,958
Ah, nothing!
I didn't say a thing!

187
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:45,250
[MAHIRU] I'm not really good
with these intense types.

188
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,750
We have a common enemy.

189
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,458
Please, help us fight him.

190
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:51,250
Your Servamp might be targeted,
just like all the others have.

191
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,625
[LAWLESS laughs]

192
00:08:52,708 --> 00:08:54,791
There's no way we'd
be able to work together.

193
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:57,750
I can already tell we'd never
see eye-to-eye on anything.

194
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,666
Right, Big Brother?

195
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,333
Anyway, you've got
Pride and Lust

196
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:03,291
on your side already, don't you?

197
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:05,875
And I guess Envy is
lurking around here, too.

198
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:08,833
That leaves Gluttony and Wrath,
who were never very smart.

199
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:10,125
But still...

200
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:10,833
Even if they are stupid,

201
00:09:12,041 --> 00:09:14,125
I bet they haven't
forgotten what you did.

202
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:15,000
[MAHIRU]
Wait...

203
00:09:15,083 --> 00:09:17,041
What's up with these two?

204
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:18,583
Why do they hate each other?

205
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:22,666
[MAHIRU] Hey! What the heck
are you talking about?

206
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:25,416
I'm Mahiru Shirota, Kuro's Eve.

207
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,125
Lawless is your nickname, right?

208
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:28,208
So what's your real name?

209
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:30,041
[LAWLESS]
O Romeo, Romeo!

210
00:09:30,125 --> 00:09:31,708
Wherefore art
thou, Romeo?

211
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,416
I mean what's in a name?

212
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,625
That which we call a rose
by any other name--

213
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,500
ah... would smell as sweet.

214
00:09:37,583 --> 00:09:39,625
Parting is such sweet sorrow.

215
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:43,166
[LAWLESS] There's no need
for you to learn my name.

216
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,750
It'll just change
again, eventually.

217
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:48,833
What does that mean?

218
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:50,916
[beeping noise]

219
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,791
Crap! It's time for work.

220
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:55,583
Damn, if I'm late,
the boss'll kill me.

221
00:09:55,666 --> 00:09:56,500
You have a job?

222
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:58,458
--See ya!
--Wait, stop!

223
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:00,416
[MAHIRU]
Why won't you help us? Please!

224
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:05,458
[LAWLESS] So you're
my brother's Eve, huh?

225
00:10:05,541 --> 00:10:07,250
But you're so normal.

226
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:14,791
[MAHIRU yells]

227
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:16,041
[TV ANNOUNCER 6A]
Jekylland Licht Todoroki,

228
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:17,708
the genius Austrian pianist,

229
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:21,125
has entranced audiences
across the globe. Now, he's...

230
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:22,416
[MAHIRU]
It's that guy!

231
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:24,041
He's not very well
known around here,

232
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:26,000
but he's super famous
back in Europe.

233
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:28,416
I hear he's something of
a young piano prodigy.

234
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,666
[TETSU]
There, all dry.

235
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,125
[MAHIRU]
I just met him earlier!

236
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,041
He's Greed's Eve!

237
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:35,041
[HUGH]
Greed, you say?

238
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,583
That's too bad.

239
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:40,708
The boy probably won't live long
enough for another concert.

240
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:42,208
Why not?

241
00:10:42,291 --> 00:10:44,541
[HUGH] Because Lawless has
a habit of killing his Eves

242
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:47,541
once he grows bored of them.

243
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:49,125
Don't worry.

244
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:52,458
He's the only Servamp who finds
pleasure in hurting his master.

245
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:55,583
He's broken. Mind and heart.

246
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:58,458
It would definitely be best
not to get mixed up with him.

247
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:06,458
[DIRECTOR 6A] We simply
cannot thank you enough.

248
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,166
You're so generous, Tsubaki.

249
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:11,250
With your continued sponsorship,
the possibilities are endless.

250
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,791
Todoroki will have a very
bright future indeed.

251
00:11:13,875 --> 00:11:15,458
Yes, I'm sure he will.

252
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:18,375
Unless something unfortunate
happens, and he dies.

253
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,833
[TSUBAKI]
The arrangements are complete.

254
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:27,291
Please take care of
the rest for me, won't you?

255
00:11:28,875 --> 00:11:30,208
[MAHIRU] Damn, looks
like there's no way I'm getting

256
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:31,791
inside without a ticket.

257
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:32,708
[KRANTZ]
Young man,

258
00:11:32,791 --> 00:11:34,333
what are you doing there?

259
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:35,833
Oh, sorry, I just, uh--

260
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:38,208
You've come to listen to
Licht's music, haven't you?

261
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:40,875
I don't have a ticket, but
I was hoping to talk to him.

262
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:43,250
Although it looks like
I'm not gonna get in here.

263
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:44,666
I see!

264
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:46,375
Actually, it's youths like you
who should be listening

265
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:48,708
to him perform;
you're the future of music.

266
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,166
Unfortunately for you,

267
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:53,000
every seat in the concert
hall has been booked today.

268
00:11:53,083 --> 00:11:54,041
But if you come with me,

269
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:56,625
I can at least get
you a program.

270
00:11:56,708 --> 00:11:58,416
Oh, thanks,
that would be awesome.

271
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,458
[MAHIRU]
Is this a good idea?

272
00:12:04,166 --> 00:12:06,041
[MAHIRU]
That's one of Tsubaki's men.

273
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,750
Why is he here?

274
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:10,083
[MAHIRU] Um... Where's
the concert taking place?

275
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:12,208
Uh, the great hall
on the basement level.

276
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:13,750
[MAHIRU]
I'm sorry!

277
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,083
[KRANTZ]
Hey, kid, wait!

278
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:16,458
[MAHIRU]
If Tsubaki's subclass is here,

279
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,000
then they must
be targeting them.

280
00:12:18,083 --> 00:12:21,041
[piano music]

281
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,583
[LAWLESS]
What's this?

282
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,583
I kinda figured you'd
come after me today,

283
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:29,000
but I didn't expect you'd
make up the entire audience.

284
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:31,125
Look, I don't have
time for this.

285
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:33,083
Not when my gloomy
angel is in the middle

286
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:35,291
of such a beautiful
performance!

287
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:38,583
[MAHIRU]
Tsubaki must know about Lawless.

288
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:41,375
And that Licht
is the Eve of Greed.

289
00:12:41,458 --> 00:12:44,000
Was the entire concert
nothing more than a trap?

290
00:12:44,083 --> 00:12:45,708
I have to make it
in time to warn them!

291
00:12:45,791 --> 00:12:46,875
And help them fight!

292
00:12:46,958 --> 00:12:49,541
[piano music]

293
00:12:54,791 --> 00:12:57,583
[LAWLESS]
Bravo! Bravo!

294
00:12:57,666 --> 00:12:59,958
Oh, there you are.
I'm afraid you missed the show.

295
00:13:00,041 --> 00:13:02,625
My angel just finished
his performance.

296
00:13:02,708 --> 00:13:04,750
[MAHIRU] All these
guys were vampires?

297
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:05,958
And you two stopped them?

298
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:07,916
[LAWLESS laughs]
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

299
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,750
This little massacre was all me.

300
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:11,000
[MAHIRU]
You're kidding me.

301
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:13,458
This seems unbelievable.
Lawless is so strong.

302
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:15,166
But maybe he went too far.

303
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:19,458
[LICHT] You were too noisy
during my performance,

304
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:20,916
you damn hedgehog.

305
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,291
I'll kill you.

306
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:23,458
[LAWLESS] I was just teaching
these rude vampires

307
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:25,083
to be a good audience.

308
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:26,208
What's wrong?

309
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,958
Where's your gratitude?

310
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:29,041
Die!

311
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:32,541
[LAWLESS]
No thanks!

312
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:35,166
[MAHIRU]
Hey! Careful!

313
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:36,625
Eves are human; you'll kill him!

314
00:13:36,708 --> 00:13:38,250
[LAWLESS]
Oh, he's fine.

315
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:40,958
Don't you know that Eves are
stronger than normal people?

316
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:45,916
Besides, if he gets hurt that
easily, then he's useless.

317
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,458
[LAWLESS] Please tell me
you're here for the music

318
00:13:47,541 --> 00:13:50,041
and not because you're still
trying to make us best buds.

319
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:51,833
All you really need is Kuro.

320
00:13:51,916 --> 00:13:54,208
[MAHIRU] Yeah, I know
that Kuro's strong.

321
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:55,833
But, this isn't the kind
of thing we can do

322
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:56,833
without more help!

323
00:13:56,916 --> 00:13:59,166
[LAWLESS]
You don't know anything.

324
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:00,583
What's wrong, brother?

325
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:02,125
Haven't you told him?

326
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,250
[MAHIRU yells]

327
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:06,958
This is a real pain.

328
00:14:07,041 --> 00:14:08,208
Kuro!

329
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:10,666
[LAWLESS] Trying to be
a hero now, eh, Sloth?

330
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:13,541
Fancy yourself as some kind
of loveable main character?

331
00:14:13,625 --> 00:14:14,541
You're crazy.

332
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:15,916
[LAWLESS]
So annoying!

333
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,375
You're concerned with the
why and when and where

334
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:19,458
and what of your story,

335
00:14:19,541 --> 00:14:21,000
but not how you'll
achieve anything

336
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:23,583
and who you're going
to become in the end.

337
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:27,083
You're just spouting hollow
ideals and playing pretend.

338
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:30,125
You have no real motivation.

339
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,833
Since you're
completely clueless,

340
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:35,250
allow me to give you
a brief history lesson.

341
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,958
A long time ago,

342
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:40,125
in a certain place
at a certain time,

343
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:43,291
there were seven
darling vampire siblings.

344
00:14:43,375 --> 00:14:46,291
Then, a single letter
arrived for us all.

345
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:50,000
It was from a supposedly
neutral party called C3.

346
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,625
C3?

347
00:14:51,708 --> 00:14:53,750
[LAWLESS]
The letter was a command.

348
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:57,416
The vampires argued
amongst themselves.

349
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,125
And it was decided
that we'd vote

350
00:14:59,208 --> 00:15:01,666
on what to do about this order.

351
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:05,500
Greed, Gluttony, and Wrath
were all against the killing.

352
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,125
They wouldn't have it!

353
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:10,250
Pride, Envy, And Lust
were all for it,

354
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:13,125
the bloodthirsty vampires.

355
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:14,583
[MAHIRU]
I can feel it.

356
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,708
Kuro's murderous intent.

357
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:19,083
It's growing fast,
all around me.

358
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:21,416
Getting stronger.

359
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,916
[MAHIRU]
Something's wrong.

360
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,041
I can't turn around.

361
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,750
I feel like if I move at all,
I'll be swallowed up.

362
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:28,583
[LAWLESS]
Well, then.

363
00:15:28,666 --> 00:15:30,583
It was three against three.

364
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,666
So what did the
eldest sibling vote?

365
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:35,583
What did he do when someone's
life was in his hands?

366
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,208
This is what that
lazy bastard had to say.

367
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:46,708
Wow, you really don't want
him to hear this story, huh?

368
00:15:46,791 --> 00:15:48,083
I'm kind of impressed.

369
00:15:48,166 --> 00:15:49,458
[laughing]

370
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:51,000
[MAHIRU] I thought we could
become allies without

371
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,750
any problems, but...

372
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:54,958
[LAWLESS]
Sleep no more!

373
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:57,000
He does murder sleep!

374
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:58,333
My poor elder brother,

375
00:15:58,416 --> 00:16:01,208
I don't think you're ever
going to find any peace!

376
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:02,666
[MAHIRU] There's so much
hostility between

377
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:04,541
the two of them.

378
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:07,625
[LAWLESS] You all want to
forget that this ever happened!

379
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:10,625
That's the thing I hate
most about you idiots!

380
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:15,583
[TSUBAKI]
Complete annihilation?

381
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:17,291
[SAKUYA] Otogiri and the
others who were outside

382
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:18,791
managed to escape.

383
00:16:18,875 --> 00:16:20,791
But everyone in the hall...

384
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:21,958
Tsu-Tsu, love.

385
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:23,875
Lawless was really strong.

386
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:26,041
[SHAMROCK]
It's true. Please forgive us.

387
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:28,958
[TSUBAKI]
I see.

388
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:32,791
Everyone, I... apologize.

389
00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:35,166
This was a terrible
miscalculation.

390
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,333
I should have waited
until Higan returned.

391
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:39,250
[SHAMROCK]
No! Young master!

392
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,916
[TSUBAKI]
I am sorry.

393
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,541
Forgive me, my family.

394
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:45,500
[LAWLESS]
Will all great Neptune's ocean


395
00:16:45,583 --> 00:16:49,083
wash this blood clean
from your hand? [laughs]


396
00:16:49,166 --> 00:16:50,125
No!

397
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:56,958
This your hand will rather the
multitudinous seas incarnadine.


398
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:59,375
Making the green one red.


399
00:16:59,458 --> 00:17:00,583
Right, brother?


400
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:02,958
[LILAC]
I can't believe it.

401
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,958
How did this go so badly?

402
00:17:05,041 --> 00:17:06,708
There were so many of us here.

403
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:09,250
Lilac!

404
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,458
It sounds like we're
going to get to go on

405
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,500
Tsubaki's next mission!
Isn't that amazing?

406
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:15,416
Yeah, he usually never lets
the weaker subclasses join in.

407
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,166
Whatever it is he's planning
must be a really big deal.

408
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:20,875
We'll finally get the chance
to make him proud of us.

409
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,541
[LILAC]
We were so excited.

410
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,458
So ready to serve.

411
00:17:24,541 --> 00:17:26,791
We were prepared for
violence and chaos.

412
00:17:26,875 --> 00:17:30,208
But didn't expect that the
tables would turn against us.

413
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:32,000
We were more than
just subclasses--

414
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:33,583
we were in this together.

415
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:34,875
They were my friends.

416
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:36,458
Why did I survive?

417
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:37,958
[crying]

418
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:41,875
[MAHIRU]
I have to stop them.

419
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:45,041
And I guess I'll have
to do it alone.

420
00:17:45,916 --> 00:17:46,958
[MAHIRU]
Kuro!

421
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:53,625
[LICHT]
Hey... I told you to shut up.

422
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:56,708
Damn demons!

423
00:17:56,791 --> 00:17:58,000
[LAWLESS]
Angel, baby!

424
00:17:58,083 --> 00:17:59,375
[LAWLESS grunts, groans]

425
00:17:59,458 --> 00:18:01,541
[LICHT] I'm tired of hearing
your voice, hedgehog.

426
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:04,250
[LICHT]
Gimme that.

427
00:18:08,791 --> 00:18:09,625
[MAHIRU]
How'd he do that?

428
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:11,458
[LICHT]
You're all too noisy!

429
00:18:11,541 --> 00:18:13,916
But I'll make sure you're quiet.

430
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:17,250
How about a little
serenade from my piano?

431
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,125
Time to cry!

432
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:22,208
[piano music]

433
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:24,250
[music continues]

434
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,291
What is this I'm feeling?

435
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,416
[MAHIRU]
My mom?

436
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,250
Why? This hurts...

437
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:39,833
[LAWLESS]
Sweet Ophelia.

438
00:18:39,916 --> 00:18:43,166
Crap, this memory is putting
me in a real bad place.

439
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:44,625
Stop.

440
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:47,333
[MAHIRU] He's making us remember
things from our pasts?

441
00:18:47,416 --> 00:18:48,625
Kuro!

442
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:51,666
[KURO grunting]

443
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,666
[LAWLESS] This is the
only song I can't stand

444
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,416
to hear you play, Licht.

445
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,125
You're forcing my hand!

446
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,041
[KRANTZ]
Gill! Stop both of them!

447
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:06,708
[BOTH grunt]

448
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:07,791
[KRANTZ]
Huzzah!

449
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:09,833
--It's you!
--Yes!

450
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:11,541
Good job, Guildenstern.

451
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:12,916
[MAHIRU]
Huh?

452
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,541
Bravo!

453
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,000
Ouch! Jeez!

454
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:18,166
How could my own
subclass do that to me?

455
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:19,666
I'll kill you.

456
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:22,333
[MAHIRU]
Kuro! Are you okay?

457
00:19:22,416 --> 00:19:24,625
Hello? Kuro?

458
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,333
[LILAC gasps]
No, don't hurt me!

459
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:29,500
[LAWLESS]
What's this?

460
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:32,000
Seems like we've got
some leftovers here.

461
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:34,041
[MAHIRU]
Stop it!

462
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:35,666
[LAWLESS]
What's your problem?

463
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:38,041
There's no reason
to let him live.

464
00:19:38,125 --> 00:19:40,250
And I have no reason
to listen to you anyway.

465
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,375
[MAHIRU] Look, he's scared,
he doesn't want to fight!

466
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:43,833
You don't need to kill him!

467
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:50,208
[LAWLESS chuckles]
Well, I guess it doesn't matter.

468
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,083
He's just a background extra.

469
00:20:00,625 --> 00:20:01,541
[KRANTZ]
Licht!

470
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:02,750
There's an entire
world out there

471
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,625
waiting to hear
you play the piano.

472
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:06,500
What were you going to do
if you injured yourself

473
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:08,000
fighting like this?

474
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:09,041
Uh, hi.

475
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:11,125
Oh. You're that kid.

476
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:15,500
My name is Rosen Krantz,
Mr. Licht's music manager.

477
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:18,000
I'm just a regular human,
not a vampire.

478
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:21,791
Oh, this big blue guy happens
to be our mascot, Whale.

479
00:20:21,875 --> 00:20:23,666
Guildenstern,
Lawless's subclass,

480
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:25,333
is the one
inside the costume.

481
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:27,041
You can call him Gill.

482
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:30,166
Uh, nice to meet you.
I'm Mahiru.

483
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,166
[KRANTZ]
We'll help you with your task.

484
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:35,083
Licht's piano is one of
humanity's treasures.

485
00:20:35,166 --> 00:20:37,625
It's my duty to make sure
both of them are safe.

486
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:39,250
The world needs his music!

487
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:40,583
Shut up, Krantz.

488
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:42,500
You don't get to decide this.

489
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:45,208
He says that, but I'll
convince him. Just you wait.

490
00:20:45,291 --> 00:20:47,500
[MAHIRU]
Thank you very much.

491
00:20:47,583 --> 00:20:48,416
[KRANTZ]
Now.

492
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,333
What shall we do
with this child?

493
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:52,541
[LILAC shrieks]
I'm sorry!

494
00:20:52,625 --> 00:20:53,541
Please don't kill me!

495
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:55,291
Don't worry,
we're not going to.

496
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:56,625
But hang on a second.

497
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:58,708
I have to talk to my
friends about what to do.

498
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:03,333
[MAHIRU]
Wait! Come back!

499
00:21:03,416 --> 00:21:05,041
Where are you going?

500
00:21:05,125 --> 00:21:06,875
I'm still not very
good with my weapon,

501
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:08,333
not like you are.

502
00:21:08,416 --> 00:21:09,458
What should I do?

503
00:21:09,541 --> 00:21:11,000
[LICHT]
Doesn't matter.

504
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:12,625
You'll never learn.

505
00:21:16,583 --> 00:21:18,250
